---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Fantasy Ranked"
  description="Fantasy Ranked is a power fantasy rankings site covering LitRPG, progression fantasy, system apocalypse, and isekai — published by Pivot Press Publishing."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[#f59e0b] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-8">About Fantasy Ranked</h1>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <section>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed">
          Fantasy Ranked is a rankings and releases tracker covering power fantasy fiction across all its major
          sub-genres: LitRPG, progression fantasy, system apocalypse, isekai, dungeon core, and harem fantasy.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          The goal is a single, cross-genre destination for readers who follow the broader power fantasy space —
          rather than being siloed into any one community or platform. Rankings are updated regularly.
          New releases are tracked from both our platforms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[#2e2e2e] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Who Publishes This Site</h2>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed">
          Fantasy Ranked is published by <strong class="text-white">Pivot Press Publishing</strong> — the team
          behind <a href="https://litrpgtools.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">LitRPGTools.com</a>
          and <a href="https://harem-lit.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">Harem-Lit.com</a>,
          and a publisher of original LitRPG fiction including titles by Aaron Renfroe, Sean Oswald, and David North.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Our editorial rankings draw on community data from both platforms. Because we also publish in the genre,
          some Pivot Press titles may appear in rankings. We include them because they belong there — every list
          is grounded in community ratings, not internal promotion.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[#2e2e2e] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Our Data</h2>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed">
          Rankings combine community rating data from
          <a href="https://litrpgtools.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">LitRPGTools.com</a>
          (LitRPG, progression fantasy, dungeon core, GameLit, system apocalypse, isekai) and
          <a href="https://harem-lit.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">Harem-Lit.com</a>
          (harem fantasy, cultivation, men's romance). Together these platforms track thousands of titles
          across the power fantasy genre with reader-sourced ratings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[#2e2e2e] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Amazon Affiliate Links</h2>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed">
          Links to Amazon on this site are affiliate links. If you click through and make a purchase,
          we may earn a small commission at no extra cost to you. This helps support the site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[#2e2e2e] pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-[#aaa] leading-relaxed">
          Questions or corrections? Visit our <a href="/contact" class="text-[#f59e0b] hover:underline">contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
